In this article, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. reflects on the impact his own father had on him and the values he passed down. He expresses gratitude and appreciation for fathers and father figures who guide and support their children. The article also acknowledges that Father's Day can be difficult for those who have lost a father or child and highlights the challenges faced by families during the pandemic. President Biden emphasizes his administration's commitment to strengthening American families and easing the burdens of caregiving, including providing paid family leave and supporting single parents. The article concludes with a proclamation officially recognizing June 20, 2021, as Father's Day and calling for the flag of the United States to be displayed on government buildings.